    <note>Xiao(1) Jian [12266] For move to Changsha (Tanzhou), see Yang Wanli, WJ, 128.9a.  For county as Liuyang, see Zhou Bida, WJ, 67.11a-11b. For link to both Jishui and Xinyu Xiao ancestors (respectively Chujun and Ji), see Wang Anshi, WJ, 93.96b. See also documentation for ancestor, Bao [12248]. It should be noted that his ancestor and founder of the Liang Dynasty, Yan [12254] (Liang Wudi), enfeoffed his elder brother, Yi(2), [12285] as Changsha Wang. In addition, the Minor Liang ( the ruling family was his direct ancestral lineage) with its capital at Jiangling probably also controlled the Changsha area. Jian, as the #1 son of Fu [12264] and probably the senior member of this lineage during his generation, might have had imperial hopes with what might have appeared at this time to be the end of Tang (pure speculation).</note>
